# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js 15+ project with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS. The project uses Bun as the package manager.

## Key Directories and Files

- [app/](mdc:app) - Contains the Next.js app router pages and layouts
- [components/](mdc:components) - React components using functional style with TypeScript
- [lib/](mdc:lib) - Utility functions and shared logic
- [public/](mdc:public) - Static assets
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind CSS configuration
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration

## Development Guidelines

1. Use functional React components with TypeScript
2. Follow mobile-first approach with Tailwind CSS
3. Use Motion (Framer Motion) for animations: `import { motion } from "motion/react"`
4. Use Bun for package management (bun.lock present)
5. Use Tailwind's built-in animation classes when possible
6. Implement hover transitions for interactive elements

## Component Standards

- All components should be TypeScript files (.tsx)
- Use proper type definitions for props
- Implement responsive design using Tailwind breakpoints
- Use Lucide React for icons when custom icons aren't required
